    'description' => 'Recursively scan a directory tree and produce comprehensive filesystem statistics. Counts files by extension, identifies largest files, calculates directory sizes, analyzes file age distribution, detects duplicate filenames, and shows type breakdowns. Uses PHP\'s RecursiveDirectoryIterator and RecursiveIteratorIterator internally — no shell commands. Composes with chart_generator (for visualization) and csv_generate (for export). First recursive filesystem analysis tool in the ecosystem. Never throws — all errors returned as structured data.',
